#%PAM-1.0
# PAM stack for the btop-lock lockscreen — invoked via pamtester from inside
# kmscon (running as root, with no logind user session). Password-only.
#
# Why not grosshack: tried `pam_fprintd_grosshack + libpinpam + pam_unix`
# (mirror of hyprlock's stack). The auth modules work, but pamtester's
# basic PAM conv function doesn't drive grosshack's interleaved fingerprint
# listener + multi-stage prompts correctly — typed input ended up buffered
# in stdin and leaked back to zsh after pamtester returned. Use case here
# is "across the room with the laptop closed" so fingerprint is useless
# anyway; physlock (in-person) still has the full stack.
auth        required     pam_unix.so
account     required     pam_unix.so
session     required     pam_unix.so
